lead_paragraph: BALTIMORE, Feb. 1 -- Forty-two tons of foodstuffs and tobacco requested by the United States Ambassador to France, Admiral William D. Leahy, for himself and members of his staff were removed from the Red Cross mercy ship Cold Harbor just before the vessel sailed for Spain this afternoon with a $1,000,000 relief cargo for Spain and France.
abstract: SS Cold Harbor sails with Brit blockade passage permit
